cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically low-level vision tasks such as image restoration, image-to-image translation, and style transfer. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for achieving smooth control of imagery effects, which could fall under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also investigates the mechanism of network interpolation, which could fall under the sub-categories cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
